cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DC 

This paper proposes a decentralized mechanism for collision avoidance among a group of independently controlled robots, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The mechanism design aspect of the proposed solution suggests that it could also be categorized under game theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions the use of path-finding algorithms, which could place it under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or distributed computing (cs.DC).
